---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="HealthDrop Privacy"
  description="Privacy policy for HealthDrop, a one-way iPhone HealthKit export utility."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="eyebrow">HealthDrop</div>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="hero-lede">
      HealthDrop is a one-way export utility for your own iPhone HealthKit data.
      It does not run analytics, ads, telemetry, or a third-party backend.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">Data Access</span>
    <p>
      HealthDrop asks for read access to selected HealthKit data: sleep, steps,
      resting heart rate, heart rate variability, and workouts. The app does
      not write data back to HealthKit.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">Data Export</span>
    <p>
      Health data leaves the device only when you press Export, and only to the
      destination you choose in the app: iCloud Drive, the iOS share sheet, or
      an HTTP endpoint you configure.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you configure an HTTP endpoint, the destination server is controlled by
      you. HealthDrop does not provide or operate a hosted ingest service.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">Storage</span>
    <p>
      Export settings are stored locally on the device. HealthDrop does not
      create a developer account, upload data to a developer server, sell data,
      or share data with advertisers or data brokers.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <span class="section-label">Contact</span>
    <p>
      For support or privacy questions, use the public contact links on the
      <a href="/healthdrop/support">HealthDrop support page</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
